    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-09T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-09T01:00:00-05:00" n="575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/7001: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-09T15:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1920—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 9—2:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>288. My May 25, 4 p.m.,<note n="45" xml:id="d575fn45">Not found in Department
                        files.</note> and June 4, 6 p.m. The War Office yesterday issued statement
                    reporting that the 100 Japanese residents who survived the Nikolaevsk massacre
                    in March were apparently <pb facs="0614" n="514" xml:id="pg_514"/> slaughtered
                    about May 25th. Public feeling is running high and demanding punitive measures
                    against Partisans. There are also suggestions in the press that northern
                    Sakhalin should be occupied as a guarantee for reparation to be exacted after a
                    Russian government, which can be dealt with, is established.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
